The paper is primarily focused on computer vision and its role in action, which suggests that it belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses immersive simulation and robotics, which are relevant to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The paper also mentions machine learning and training sensorimotor systems, which are relevant to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses achieving higher task performance and generalization, which are relevant to the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category.
